        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>
                    <exhotlnk document="../afcs/AFC01905.pdf" bookname="AFC">Print ready (PDF file) copy of the AFC
                        letter
                    </exhotlnk>
                </para>
                <para>When installing the bulb connector to the headlamp assembly, the blades of the bulb terminals may
                    have poor electrical contact with the harness connector resulting in heat build up and distortion of
                    the connector body. Proper headlamp operation may be noted, however, progressive damage may occur
                    with subsequent loss of headlamp illumination.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
