        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
            <title>INSPECTION</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury, park the vehicle on a flat level surface and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open the vehicle hood and remove the headlamp bulb access cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the headlamp harness connector:</para>
                <seqlist>
                    <item>
                        <para>If the harness connector is colored blue,
                            <emph type="bold">no replacement is required.</emph>
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If the harness connector body is colored black with a dark blue seal (see arrow in Figure
                            1), the headlamp assembly must be replaced. Proceed to the Service Procedure.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </seqlist>
                <figure id="f019057" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g019057.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Headlamp Connector Seal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="5">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the vehicle approximately 25 feet away from a clean wall or door. With the hood
                    down and latched, turn on the headlamps and draw a line on the wall or door at the top of both
                    headlamp beams for reference.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the hood in the closed position, remove the four grille mounting screws (Figure 2,
                    Item 3).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the grille by lifting the grille up and outward from the mounting tabs (Figure 2,
                    Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f019051" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g019051.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Grille Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GRILLE MOUNTING TABS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOWER GRILLE MOUNTING POINTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. GRILLE MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform each Step of this procedure to the headlamp assembly on both the passenger and driver
                        side before proceeding to the next Step.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the hood in the open position, remove three headlamp mounting nuts on the backside
                    of the headlamp assembly (Figure 3).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f019052" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g019052.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Backside of Headlamp Assembly (Partial View)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEADLAMP MOUNTING NUTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the headlamp assembly harness connector located near each side of the
                    radiator (Figure 4).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f019053" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0900312.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Headlamp Harness Connector</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RADIATOR MOUNTING BLOCK</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HARNESS CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TOP OF FRAME RAIL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Move the hood to the closed position and remove the headlamp mounting bolt from the
                    fender assembly (Figure 5).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f019054" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g019054.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Headlamp Assembly, Arrow Indicates Mounting Bolt</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the headlamp assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new headlamp assembly by following the preceding Steps in reverse order.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the grille.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the hood closed and latched, turn on the headlamps and match the headlamp beams to
                    the reference lines drawn in Step 1. Adjust the headlamp beam height as needed by turning the
                    adjustment screw on the backside of the headlamp assembly (Figure 6).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Perform the same procedure to the headlamp on the opposite side.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f019055" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g019055.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Headlamp Adjustment</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ADJUSTMENT SCREW</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
